Insert simmering basket and add leeks and red peppers to it. Set Varoma containing ramekins in position and steam <b>18 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep flans warm. Remove simmering basket using spatula and set aside. Empty and clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Yoghurt sauce"},{"content":"Place goat’s cheese, plain yoghurt, chives, salt and ground pepper in mixing bowl and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste."},{"content":"Unmould flans by running a small thin knife around the inside edge of each ramekin, then place a plate on top of each ramekin and turn it over, carefully helping flan out of ramekin with knife if necessary. Arrange steamed leeks and red peppers around flans, drizzle with sauce and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The flans can also be served cold as a starter, with lettuce and diced tomatoes.<br>- For a stronger flavour, replace goat’s cheese with <b>90 g blue<b> cheese (e.g. Gorgonzola) in the flan and <b>60 g blue<b> cheese in the yoghurt sauce.<br>- To make your own yoghurt, refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook.<\/i>"],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","45m","4 portions"]}